ram the small commercial business segment offers workers’ compensation insurance products and commercial package insurance products such as commercial property general liability inland marine automobile and umbrella coverage as well as other property and casualty insurance products to small businesses the specialty risk and extended warranty segment provides coverage for consumer and commercial goods custom design amtrust financial services inc through its subsidiaries underwrites and provides property and casualty insurance in the united states and internationally it operates in three segments small commercial business specialty risk and extended warranty and specialty program the small commercial business segment offers workers’ compensation insurance products and commercial package insurance products such as commercial property general liability inland marine automobile and umbrella coverage as well as other property and casualty insurance products to small businesses the specialty risk and extended warranty segment provides coverage for consumer and commercial goods custom designed coverages such as accidental damage plans and payment protection plans and coverage for niche property and casualty risks as well as specialty liability risks comprising general liability employers’ liability and professional and medical liability this segment also serves as a third party administrator to provide claims handling and call center services to the consumer products and automotive industries the specialty program segment provides workers’ compensation general liability commercial auto liability property coverage excess and surplus lines programs and other specialty commercial property and casualty insurance products to small and middle market companies the company also provides reinsurance services primarily for personal and commercial automotive business it distributes its policies through a network of retail and wholesale agents as well as through thirdparty brokers agents retailers or administrators amtrust financial services inc was founded in  and is based in new york new york detailed description  maiden lanerd floornew york ny united statesfounded in  employees phone  fax  wwwamtrustgroupcom key executives for amtrust financial services inc mr barry d zyskind chairman of the board chief executive officer and president age  total annual compensation k mr adam karkowsky cfo  executive vp age  total annual compensation k mr christopher m longo chief operating officer chief information officer and executive vice president age  total annual compensation k mr max g caviet chief executive officer of amtrust international limited age  total annual compensation k mr david h saks chief legal officer and executive vice president age  total annual compensation m compensation as of fiscal year  amtrust financial services inc key developments amtrust financial services inc appoints j daniel hickey as executive vice president business strategy and business development jul   amtrust financial services inc announced that j daniel hickey a senior insurance industry executive has joined company as executive vice president business strategy and business development mr hickey will oversee the company’s business strategy planning function developing and implementing a global strategic framework for amtrust that reflects macro market trends and local market insights he will also be responsible for amtrust’s business development identifying and managing key partner relationships as well as organic business opportunities available to amtrust throughout its global business platform he previously served at partnerre mr hickey is based at amtrust’s new york city headquarters and reports directly to mr zyskind chairman and chief executive officer of amtrust amtrust financial services inc presents at the william blair  growth stock conference jun  pm jun   amtrust financial services inc presents at the william blair  growth stock conference jun  pm venue t